.TH MAKE\-DATA\-DIRS 1 "April 2026" "DAQ-ControlRoom" "Mu2e DAQ Utilities"
.SH NAME
make\-data\-dirs \- create the standard Mu2e DAQ data directory hierarchy
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B make\-data\-dirs.sh
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B make\-data\-dirs.sh
is a Python script (with a
.I .sh
extension) that creates the canonical directory tree used by the Mu2e DAQ
system for storing run data.
.PP
The hierarchy is built by combining three orthogonal lists:
.TP
.B Data area prefixes
.BR data ,\  data\-2 ,\  test\-data ,\  scratch
.TP
.B Run types
.BR test ,\  prod ,\  commissioning ,\  study ,\  other
.TP
.B Detector subsystems
.BR calo ,\  trk ,\  crv ,\  stm ,\  extmon ,\  aux ,\  other
.PP
Every combination is created as an absolute path of the form:
.PP
.nf
/\fIprefix\fR/\fIruntype\fR/\fIdetector\fR/
.fi
.PP
Directories that already exist are left unchanged
.RB ( os.makedirs
is called with
.BR exist_ok=True ).
Errors creating individual directories are printed and the script continues
with the remaining paths.
.PP
Because paths begin with
.BR / ,
the script must be run as a user with write permission to the top-level
directories (typically
.B root
or with appropriate group permissions on the DAQ cluster).
.SH PREREQUISITES
.TP
.B Python 3
Standard library only; no additional packages are required.
.SH EXIT STATUS
Always exits 0.
Individual directory-creation failures are printed to standard output but
do not stop the script or change the exit code.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Create the full data directory tree:
.PP
.nf
sudo python3 make\-data\-dirs.sh
.fi
.PP
Preview the paths without creating them (dry-run using Python):
.PP
.nf
python3 \- <<'EOF'
prefixList = ["data","data-2","test-data","scratch"]
runtype    = ["test","prod","commissioning","study","other"]
detList    = ["calo","trk","crv","stm","extmon","aux","other"]
for p in prefixList:
    for r in runtype:
        for d in detList:
            print(f"/{p}/{r}/{d}/")
EOF
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR mkdir (1),
.BR install (1)
